channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Focus Groups and Snap Polls About VP Debate Are Going to Make Dems Tear Their Hair Out
Biden, Harris head to hurricane-ravaged Southeast in wake of Trump visit
item.description: President Biden and Vice President Harris each travel to the storm-ravaged Southeast on Wednesday, two days after Donald Trump visited â€“ as the death toll and devastation from Hurricane Helene soars.

item.title: Experts Agree, It Was Vance's Big Night
item.description: No sooner had J.D. Vance and Tim Walz shaken hands after concluding the lone vice-presidential debate of the year Tuesday night than the verdict from Newsmax's panel of political scientists came in and was unanimous: the night belonged to Vance.

item.title: Doug Emhoff Reportedly Slapped Ex-Girlfriend 'So Hard She Spun Around' in Public Altercation in 2012
Vance addresses previous criticism of Trump: 'I was wrong about Donald Trump'
item.description: Republican Sen. JD Vance of Ohio said he was "wrong about Donald Trump" in the past. only coming around after the former president "delivered for the American people."

item.title: Pa. Town Grapples With Trump Assassination Attempt Amid His Return
item.description: Donald Trump is going back to Butler, where the world last saw him pump his fist and beseech followers to "fight," even as blood streaked his face from a would-be assassin's bullet. In announcing his return, the former president and current Republican nominee said he planned...

item.title: Voters react to JD Vance claiming he and Donald Trump support 'clean air, clean water'
item.description: JD Vance said at the CBS Vice Presidential Debate that he and Donald Trump support "clean air, clean water," prompting mixed reactions from voters.

item.title: Biden Admin Races to Spend Climate Cash
item.description: Fearing that Donald Trump could kill off green initiatives if he wins the U.S. election, President Joe Biden's administration is racing to spend the tens of billions of dollars it had earmarked for climate action.

item.title: MSNBC's Must-See Post-Debate Meltdown Managed to Be Both Hilarious and Educational
Voters react to Gov Tim Walz dodging Tiananmen Square question: 'I'm a knucklehead at times'
item.description: A focus group of voters were skeptical of Gov. Tim Walz's explanation for falsely claiming to have been in Hong Kong during the Tiananmen Square massacre.

item.title: Biden to Visit Carolinas as Helene Death Toll Reaches 166
item.description: Many residents of the Carolinas still lacked running water, cellphone service, and electricity Wednesday as rescuers searched for people unaccounted for after Hurricane Helene caused catastrophic damage across the Southeast and killed at least 166 people.

item.title: WATCH: Walz Even Has Trouble With Questions in Pizza Shop After the Debate
Several questions about Walz's record not asked about during vice presidential debate
item.description: Several controversial moments from Gov. Tim Walz's past were not mentioned during the first and only vice presidential debate on Tuesday night in New York City.

item.title: Walz Answers on Embellishments: I'm a 'Knucklehead'
item.description: Tuesday night's vice-presidential debate between Sen. J.D. Vance, R-Ohio, and Minnesota Democrat Gov. Tim Walz focused on the issues including abortion, immigration, and foreign policy, but among the top five takeaways was Walz's answer for his past embellishments.
